    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>cauliflower florets</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>grated</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese </strong>to a large bowl with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy coated cauliflower</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tarragon-pesto-orzo-with-cheesy-crunchy-cauliflower/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cheesy coated cauliflower </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a little <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and put in the oven for 20-22 min or until the cauliflower is tender and the breadcrumbs are golden \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesey crunchy cauliflower</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tarragon-pesto-orzo-with-cheesy-crunchy-cauliflower/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the cauliflower cooks, add your <strong>orzo</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the orzo for 6-8 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the orzo and return to the pot, reserving a cup of starchy pasta water</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tarragon-pesto-orzo-with-cheesy-crunchy-cauliflower/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tarragon-pesto-orzo-with-cheesy-crunchy-cauliflower/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> basil </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tarragon-pesto-orzo-with-cheesy-crunchy-cauliflower/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the cauliflower is nearly ready, return the orzo to a low heat</p><p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>soft cheese </strong>and stir it all together</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tarragon-pesto-orzo-with-cheesy-crunchy-cauliflower/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> parsley & tarragon pesto</strong>, <strong>wilted spinach </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped basil </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy tarragon pesto orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the <strong>reserved starchy pasta</strong> <strong>water</strong> if it is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tarragon-pesto-orzo-with-cheesy-crunchy-cauliflower/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy tarragon pesto orzo </strong>and top with the <strong>cheesy crunchy cauliflower</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped basil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
